<p><strong>Brisbane, {{ date | readableDate }}</strong>
<p>OneQode is pleased to announce that construction is underway of <strong>Core Central</strong>, a brand new data centre facility for global real-time applications.</p>
<p>Strategically located <strong>just 6,371 km from Guam, Los Angeles and London</strong>, the server facility is set to transform real-time global connectivity.</p>
<div class="callout col-xs-12 p-2 my-2" id="key-facts">
	<h2>Key facts</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>OneQode is constructing a global central data centre, Core Central.</li>
		<li>Average latency to major capitals is expected to be 45ms</li>
		<li>The facility unlocks truly international multiplayer, real-time applications</li>
		<li>OneQode also introduces an advanced tool for the construction of data centres in new locations</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2 class="h3 mt-4">A central location for the world’s gamers</h2>
<p>Core Central is the world's first data centre built from the ground down for low latency connectivity, high performance, and next-gen cooling.</p>
