<p>Core Central will be launching following winter as cooler temperatures assist in the initial build phase.</p>
<p>The design and challenges of building a central server location is familiar to OneQode, as Core Central is a step forward in our philosophy pioneered by <a href="/guam/">APAC Central</a>, a central server location for Asia-Pacific, built on Guam.</p>
<h2 class="h3 mt-4">Bringing humanity closer together</h2>
<p>“Core Central represents a step beyond anything anyone has done before,” says OneQode CEO Matt Shearing “with unique logistical challenges that go far beyond import taxes.”</p>
<p>Preliminary numbers show that the Core Central data centre will be able to reach global users at a <strong>ping as low as 45ms</strong> average.</p>
<h2 class="h3 mt-4">Construction underway</h2>
<p>Properly compensated interns with training in excavation will be using state of the art S.P.A.D.Es (Solid Plank Apparatus Digging Equipment) technology, as developed by OneQode, to build an access elevator to the data centre.</p>
<p>“The S.P.A.D.E was heavily inspired by my days working in mining,” says OneQode Head of Operations Prakash V “and drew on years of study of what works best in the field of excavation. We just call it what it is.”</p>
